<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,328,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A moderately large-bodied, long-tailed species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1214,191,216]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1214,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Bradypodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
demonstrating the characteristics of the genus (Tilbury 
<emphasis box="[611,675,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[684,751,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="2006.0">2006</number>
). This species differs from its various congeners in the following respects: the adults have a relatively tall casque angled at (usually) over 
<number box="[1133,1162,268,294]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="30.0">30</number>
degrees or more to the supra-orbital line in keeping with 
<number box="[560,575,306,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="6.0">6</number>
other South African species - viz: 
<taxonomicName authority="Boulenger 1887" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1887" box="[996,1397,306,332]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="damaranum">
<emphasis box="[996,1174,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. damaranum</emphasis>
(Boulenger 
<number box="[1325,1388,306,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Raw 1976" authorityName="Raw" authorityYear="1976" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dracomontanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. dracomontanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Raw" box="[360,488,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="55" refString="Raw, L. R. G. (1976) A survey of the dwarf chameleons of Natal, South Africa, with the description of three new species (Sauria: Chamaeleonidae). Durban Museum Novitates, 11, 139 - 161." type="journal article" year="1976">
Raw 
<number box="[424,488,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, some 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray 1845" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1845" box="[575,874,345,371]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ventrale">
<emphasis box="[575,711,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. ventrale</emphasis>
(Gray 
<number box="[800,866,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1845.0">1845</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Raw 1976" authorityName="Raw" authorityYear="1976" box="[888,1214,345,371]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thamnobates">
<emphasis box="[888,1080,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. thamnobates</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Raw" box="[1088,1214,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="55" refString="Raw, L. R. G. (1976) A survey of the dwarf chameleons of Natal, South Africa, with the description of three new species (Sauria: Chamaeleonidae). Durban Museum Novitates, 11, 139 - 161." type="journal article" year="1976">
Raw 
<number box="[1153,1214,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzsimons 1930" authorityName="Fitzsimons" authorityYear="1930" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="transvaalense">
<emphasis box="[1230,1437,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. transvaalense</emphasis>
(Fitzsimons 
<number box="[296,356,384,410]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1930.0">1930</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Raw, 1978" authorityName="Raw" authorityYear="1978" box="[421,696,384,410]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis box="[421,564,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. nemorale</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Raw" box="[571,696,384,410]" pageId="5" pageNumber="55" refString="Raw, L. R. G. (1978) A further new dwarf chameleon from Natal, South Africa (Sauria: Chamaeleonidae). Durban Museum Novitates, 11, 265 - 269." type="journal article" year="1978">
Raw, 
<number box="[637,696,384,410]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Qudeni ecomorph). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1247,384,409]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ventrale">
<emphasis box="[1118,1247,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. ventrale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has a tail that is less than 
<number box="[342,373,422,448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="50.0">50</number>
% of its snout /vent length; from 
<taxonomicName box="[767,951,423,448]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thamnobates">
<emphasis box="[767,951,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. thamnobates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has prominent enlarged plate-like flank tubercles; from 
<taxonomicName box="[407,583,461,486]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="damaranum">
<emphasis box="[407,583,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. damaranum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has areas of “naked” interstitium around the axilla and along the anterior para-vertebral zone; from 
<taxonomicName box="[560,704,500,525]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis box="[560,704,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has a relatively much reduced gular crest, and a dorsal crest of cones larger than the diameter of the eye-opening; and from 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1179,538,563]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Bradypodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="transvaalense">
<emphasis box="[979,1179,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">B. transvaalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu stricta) where most adult specimens usually have dorsal cones larger than the eye opening and in which the superior temporal zone is pale coloured and the black mid-temporal stripe continues uninterrupted over the upper and mid flank (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,395,654,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<figureCitation box="[281,386,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1548,1572]" captionTargetBox="[284,1322,739,1524]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[264,1323,709,1524]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Head detail of Bradypodion ngomeense sp. nov. Adult male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190210/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
Figure 
<number box="[371,386,654,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
